The paper deals with designing effective architectures for deep neural networks, which is a common topic in machine learning and computer vision research. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves optimization and search algorithms, which are relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the use of reinforcement learning, which is a common technique in natural language processing research, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) a possible sub-category as well.
